A group of learners staged the demonstration over the hostel superintendent's alleged misconduct. CAPE TOWN - Protesting Wynberg Girls High school learners have dispersed following a picket outside the school on Friday afternoon.The group staged the demonstration over the hostel superintendent's alleged misconduct.Last week, pupils released a statement claiming they are victims of sexual abuse and racism at the school. Education MEC spokesperson Jessica Shelver says: There were about 20 learners from Wynberg Girls' High School who protested peacefully outside the school. This was in light of a statement they released, highlighting allegations of racism, discrimination and misconduct against the superintendent of the school hostel. We all wholeheartedly support the learners democratic rights to protest. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)